#: ../../asset_management/dam_overview.rst:19
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#: ../../asset_management/dam_overview.rst:21
msgid ""
"Can you find your digital photographs when you need them? Or do you spend "
"more time sifting through your hard drive and file cabinets than you would "
"like? Do you have a systematic approach for assigning and tracking content "
"data on your photos? If you make a living as a photographer, do your images "
"bear your copyright and contact information, or do they circulate in the "
"marketplace unprotected? Do you want your future grandchildren to admire "
"your photographs you have taken yesterday? How do you ensure backup and the "
"correctness of your data? How to prepare to change your computer, your hard "
"disk, the software, the operating system and still manage to find your "
"pictures or movies?"
msgstr ""
"Ali lahko najdete svoje digitalne fotografije, ko jih potrebujete? Ali pa "
"porabite več časa za brskanje po trdem disku in omarah za datoteke, kot bi "
"si želeli? Ali imate sistematičen pristop pri dodeljevanju in sledenju "
"vsebinskih podatkov na vaših fotografijah? Če se preživljate kot fotograf, "
"ali vaše slike nosijo vaše avtorske pravice in kontaktne podatke ali krožijo "
"na trgu nezaščitene? Si želite, da vaši bodoči vnuki občudujejo vaše "
"fotografije, ki ste jih posneli včeraj? Kako zagotavljate varnostno "
"kopiranje in pravilnost svojih podatkov? Kako se pripraviti na menjavo "
"računalnika, trdega diska, programske opreme, operacijskega sistema in "
"vseeno uspeti najti svoje slike ali filme?"

#: ../../asset_management/dam_overview.rst:24
msgid "Definitions"
msgstr "Definicije"

#: ../../asset_management/dam_overview.rst:26
msgid ""
"Digital Asset Management (DAM) refers to every part of the process that "
"follows the taking of the picture, all the way through the final output and "
"permanent storage. Anyone who shoots, scans or stores digital photographs is "
"practicing some form of DAM, but most of us are not doing so in a systematic "
"or efficient way."
msgstr ""
"Upravljanje digitalnih sredstev (DAM) se nanaša na vsak del postopka, ki "
"sledi fotografiranju, vse do končnega izpisa in trajnega shranjevanja. "
"Vsakdo, ki fotografira, skenira ali shranjuje digitalne fotografije, izvaja "
"neko obliko DAM, vendar večina od nas tega ne počne na sistematičen ali "
"učinkovit način."

#: ../../asset_management/dam_overview.rst:28
msgid "A generic definition of DAM:"
msgstr "Splošna definicija DAM:"

#: ../../asset_management/dam_overview.rst:30
msgid ""
"Digital Asset Management ingests, indexes, categorizes, secures, searches, "
"transforms, assembles and exports content that has monetary or cultural "
"value."
msgstr ""
"Digital Asset Management zaužije, indeksira, kategorizira, varuje, išče, "
"preoblikuje, sestavlja in izvaža vsebino, ki ima denarno ali kulturno "
"vrednost."

#: ../../asset_management/dam_overview.rst:32
msgid "And since we're at it another important one:"
msgstr "In ko smo že pri drugem pomembnem:"

#: ../../asset_management/dam_overview.rst:34
msgid ""
"Metadata is defined as data about data. Metadata is definitional data that "
"provides information about or documentation of other data managed within an "
"application or environment."
msgstr ""
"Metapodatki so definirani kot podatki o podatkih. Metapodatki so "
"definicijski podatki, ki zagotavljajo informacije ali dokumentacijo o drugih "
"podatkih, upravljanih znotraj aplikacije ali okolja."

#: ../../asset_management/dam_overview.rst:36
msgid "In our context here it stands for all information about a photograph."
msgstr "V našem kontekstu tukaj pomeni vse informacije o fotografiji."

#: ../../asset_management/dam_overview.rst:39
msgid "DAM and digiKam"
msgstr "DAM in digiKam"

#: ../../asset_management/dam_overview.rst:41
msgid ""
"In this section of the manual, we will present the **tools** and the "
"**practical advices** on how to **file**, **find**, **protect** and **re-"
"use** photographs, focusing on best practices for digital photographers "
"using digiKam. We cover **downloading**, **renaming**, **culling**, "
"**converting**, **grouping**, **backing-up**, **rating**, **tagging**, "
"**archiving**, **optimizing**, **maintaining** and **exporting** item files."
msgstr ""
"V tem delu priročnika bomo predstavili **orodja** in **praktične nasvete** o "
"tem, kako **shraniti**, **poiskati**, **zaščititi** in **ponovno uporabiti** "
"fotografije, s poudarkom na najboljših praksah za digitalne fotografe, ki "
"uporabljajo digiKam. Pokrivamo **prenos**, **preimenovanje**, **izločanje**, "
"**pretvorbo**, **združevanje**, **varnostno kopiranje**, **ocenjevanje**, "
"**označevanje* *, **arhiviranje**, **optimiziranje**, **vzdrževanje** in "
"**izvažanje** datotek elementov."

#: ../../asset_management/dam_overview.rst:43
msgid ""
"digiKam with its libraries and tools is a unique and comprehensive tool to "
"cover most of DAM tasks, and it does it fast and transparently. Based on "
"open standards on all fronts it will not confine you to a platform or "
"application, rather it puts you into a fast track to manage and find your "
"photographs and to move on if you so please to any other platform, "
"application, system without losing any of your work be it as an occasional "
"user, enthusiast or professional."
msgstr ""
"digiKam s svojimi knjižnicami in orodji je edinstveno in celovito orodje, ki "
"pokriva večino nalog DAM, in to opravi hitro in pregledno. Na podlagi "
"odprtih standardov na vseh frontah vas ne bo omejil na platformo ali "
"aplikacijo, temveč vas postavi na hitro pot do upravljanja in iskanja vaših "
"fotografij ter nadaljevanja, če želite, na katero koli drugo platformo, "
"aplikacijo ali sistem brez izgube kateregakoli vašega dela, pa naj bo to kot "
"občasni uporabnik, navdušenec ali profesionalec."

#: ../../asset_management/dam_overview.rst:49
msgid ""
"digiKam :ref:`Advanced Search Tool <advanced_search>` Locating Several Items "
"in Database by Photograph Properties"
msgstr ""
"digiKam :ref:`Orodje za napredno iskanje <advanced_search>` Iskanje več "
"elementov v zbirki podatkov glede na lastnosti fotografije"

#: ../../asset_management/dam_overview.rst:51
msgid ""
"The one thing that differentiates the archiving capabilities of film versus "
"digital is that with digital you can make as many new originals as you want. "
"With film you only have one original. All copies will have a slightly lower "
"quality, and both originals and copies are more or less slowly aging and "
"disappearing. The only way to keep it *forever fresh* is to make a digital "
"copy of it. And that is also the only way to protect it from all hazards."
msgstr ""
"Edina stvar, po kateri se zmožnosti arhiviranja filma razlikujejo od "
"digitalnih, je ta, da lahko z digitalnim ustvarite toliko novih izvirnikov, "
"kot želite. Pri filmu imate samo en original. Vse kopije bodo nekoliko "
"slabše kakovosti, tako originali kot kopije pa se bolj ali manj počasi "
"starajo in izginjajo. Edini način, da ostane *večno svež*, je, da naredite "
"njegovo digitalno kopijo. In to je tudi edini način, da ga zaščitimo pred "
"vsemi nevarnostmi."

#: ../../asset_management/dam_overview.rst:53
msgid ""
"Even if digital media today may last shorter than film it is just up to you "
"to make new copies every year, 5, 10 years or whenever necessary, and to "
"always keep at least 2-3 copies of the files, preferably in different "
"physical locations. You never had that opportunity with film. It could "
"always be damaged in a fire, floods or similar - or even be stolen. The good "
"and bad news then is this: if you lose digital images/data it is only your "
"own laxity."
msgstr ""
"Tudi če digitalni mediji danes morda trajajo krajše od filma, je samo na "
"vas, da naredite nove kopije vsako leto, 5, 10 let ali kadar koli je to "
"potrebno, in da vedno hranite vsaj 2-3 kopije datotek, po možnosti na "
"različnih fizičnih lokacijah. Te priložnosti s filmom niste nikoli imeli. "
"Vedno se lahko poškoduje v požaru, poplavi ali podobno – ali pa ga celo "
"ukradejo. Dobra in slaba novica je torej naslednja: če izgubite digitalne "
"slike/podatke, je to samo vaša zanikrnost."
